Fixes #99


As of January 1 2019, Mozilla requires that all GitHub projects include this [CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md](https://github.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) file in the project root. The file has two parts:

1. Required Text - All text under the headings *Community Participation Guidelines and How to Report*, are required, and should not be altered.
2. Optional Text - The Project Specific Etiquette heading provides a space to speak more specifically about ways people can work effectively and inclusively together. Some examples of those can be found on the [Firefox Debugger](https://github.com/devtools-html/debugger.html/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md) project, and [Common Voice](https://github.com/mozilla/voice-web/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md). (The optional part is commented out in the [raw template file](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mozilla/repo-templates/blob/master/templates/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md), and will not be visible until you modify and uncomment that part.)

If you have any questions about this file, or Code of Conduct policies and procedures, please see [Mozilla-GitHub-Standards](https://wiki.mozilla.org/GitHub/Repository_Requirements) or email Mozilla-GitHub-Standards+CoC@mozilla.com.

_(Message COC002)_

pull_commit_message: Add Clogger for holding cset logging information.
Move clogger to it's own file, and have try/except blocks output warnings instead of errors.
Review changes for test_clogger.py, and add flags to disable workers temporarily.

Clogger review changes.

More specifically, this patch does the following:
  (1): Changes the use of two Lock's to one.
  (2): Enables use table dropping algorithm for update revnums.
  (3): Removes uses of str in Log calls.
  (4): Changes where the csetLog table is created to `clogger.py`.
  (5): Removes Clogger constants from service.py.
  (6): Changes revnum definition to always be the max(revnum) from the csetLog table.
Add partial tip filling test, and fixes for it.
Revert changes to service.py until a future patch.
Add tests for getting (revnum,revision) ranges or ordered lists.
Change lists to queues and wait for elements to be added before processing.
Undo hard-coded revision in clogger tests.
Delete annotations and latestFileMod entries that are too old, and add a test for this.
Simplify some logic, and add quote_set function.

pullsbody: py.test is very picky about filenames. These changes allow it to run the tests.

* the `__init__.py` file will ensure `tests` is a module
* renamed "playground" to something that starts with "test" so the unittest tool can find it.
* un-commented tests so they can be run

```
    python -m unittest tests.test_grab_tids.TestgrabTIDs.test_grabRevision
```

or run them all

```
    python -m unittest discover tests
```
